philosopher /fɪˈlɒsəfə/

(philosophers) 

1. N-COUNT A philosopher is a person who studies or writes about philosophy. 哲学家 

例： ...the Greek philosopher Plato. …希腊哲学家柏拉图。 

2. N-COUNT If you refer to someone as a philosopher , you mean that they think deeply and seriously about life and other basic matters. 哲人 

例： Carlos was something of a philosopher. 卡洛斯有几分哲人气质。

